HEADWORD: Pyre
<hw>Pyre</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>pure</ets>, Gr.
<?/, fr. <?/ fire. See <er>Fire</er>.]</ety> <def>A funeral pile; a
combustible heap on which the dead are burned; hence, any pile to be
burnt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For nine long nights, through all the dusky air,⟦br⟧
The <qex>pyres</qex> thick flaming shot a dismal glare.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pyrena</ent>⟦br⟧
